sentences.sentence:
Section 22(1) provides that a person satisfies the residence requirement for the purpose of s 21 if three prerequisites are satisfied, namely: (a) the person was present in Australia for the period of four years immediately before the day the person made the application;
(b) the person was not present in Australia as an unlawful non-citizen at any time during that four year period; and
(c) the person was present in Australia as a permanent resident for the period of 12 months immediately before the day the person made the application.
